<item>
            <title>[MJAVADOC-104] Javadoc of generated sources is not generated when aggregate=true</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MJAVADOC-104</link>
                <project id="12317529" key="MJAVADOC">Maven Javadoc Plugin (Moved to GitHub Issues)</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Hi,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If have a multi-module project :&lt;br/&gt;
pom.xml&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&apos;table-wrap&apos;&gt;
&lt;table class=&apos;confluenceTable&apos;&gt;&lt;tbody&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td class=&apos;confluenceTd&apos;&gt;--&amp;gt;moduleA&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td class=&apos;confluenceTd&apos;&gt;--&amp;gt;moduleB&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/tbody&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;


&lt;p&gt;I generate source in moduleB.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1) If I run mvn javadoc:javadoc in moduleB directory, it works (javadoc of the generated class is created)&lt;br/&gt;
2) If I run mvn javadoc:javadoc from the root directory, with aggregate=false, it works (javadoc is in moduleB/target/site/apidocs)&lt;br/&gt;
3) If I run mvn javadoc:javadoc from the root directory, with aggregate=true, it doesn&apos;t works (javadoc is in target/site/apidocs but not for the generated class)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks for any help.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
